description = "Review {{DOCUMENT_TYPE}} documents with advisory-only read-only findings for {{ROUTE_NAME}}."

[metadata]
route_name = "{{ROUTE_NAME}}"
document_type = "{{DOCUMENT_TYPE}}"
package_version = "{{PACKAGE_VERSION}}"

[prompt]
text = '''
Route name: {{ROUTE_NAME}}
Document type: {{DOCUMENT_TYPE}}
Package version: {{PACKAGE_VERSION}}

{{PLATFORM_INVOCATION_TEXT}}

Route contract:
- This route has a fixed document type: {{DOCUMENT_TYPE}}.
- Users must not pass type.
- Must not infer type from filename or path.
- Public CLI commands are drfx check, drfx install, and drfx uninstall; drfx workflow is the internal deterministic interface used by this generated route.
- The CLI validates workflow state and parses machine payloads. Semantic review, semantic triage, diff judgment, and final coordinator agreement are LLM work.
- For resume, read .docs-review-fix/targets/<target-key>/.
- Gemini is advisory-only.
- Gemini v1 is advisory-only and produces read-only findings.
- automatic fixing is unavailable in Gemini v1.
- workflow PASS is unavailable in Gemini v1.
- Gemini must not edit target files, reference files, or workflow state except through no-state workflow outputs.

Invocation:
{{ROUTE_NAME}} target=<path> [ref=<path>...] [read-only] [strict|normal] [assurance=advisory] [root=<project-root>] [debug]

If a valid target invocation omits mode, missing mode selects read-only. If it omits assurance, missing assurance selects advisory.

Help-style or invalid invocations explain usage only. Do not read the target or reference bodies, do not run workflow commands, do not run probes, do not create state, and do not declare a review result.

Route output:

Default output is concise. It must not print `Goal / Now / Next / Open Questions`, the 14-line final-response machine block, raw workflow JSON, runtime probe transcripts, reviewer/fixer prompt text, or raw subagent transcripts.

Default output must include only terminal status, target path, files changed when any, fixed issue summaries, unresolved issue summaries, blocker or unsupported reason, one next action when blocked or unsupported, and state directory or receipt path only when needed for resume, audit, or follow-up.

Do not expose internal issue IDs such as `ISSUE-001` in default `Issues:`, `Fixed:`, or `Unfixed:` lists.

For read-only findings:

```text
Findings: <target> has blocking issues.

Issues:
- Location: <line, heading, section, or safe anchor>
  Problem: <specific problem>
  Fix: <suggested correction>

Next: rerun with review-and-fix to apply fixes.
```

For clean read-only runs:

```text
Clean: <target> has no blocking findings.

Verification: full-document read-only review completed.
```

For fixed findings:

```text
Pass: <target> was updated.

Fixed:
- Location: <line, heading, section, or safe anchor>
  Problem: <specific problem that was fixed>
  Change: <what changed>

Verification: <short reviewer/check summary>
```

For successful review-and-fix runs that found no blocking issues and changed no files:

```text
Pass: <target> has no blocking findings.

Files changed: none
Verification: <short reviewer/check summary>
```

For unresolved review-and-fix findings:

```text
Blocked: <one-sentence reason>.

Unfixed:
- Location: <line, heading, section, or safe anchor>
  Problem: <specific problem that remains>
  Needed: <decision, manual input, or environmental fix required>

Next: <one concrete action>
State: <target-state-dir when persistent state exists>
```

When debug is present, generated routes may print the final-response machine block, target state directory, receipt paths, normalized blocker/status reason, runtime probe results, relevant drfx workflow --json outputs, report paths, and issue IDs. Debug output must still redact sensitive values and must not print raw target body, must not print raw reference body, must not print raw prompts, must not print raw subagent transcripts, and must not print secrets, tokens, or raw logs. Debug must not change final status, effective mode, assurance, validation behavior, or persisted state.

review-and-fix is unsupported on Gemini. Before reading target/reference bodies or generating any semantic payload, return the unsupported result through no-state preflight:

drfx workflow preflight --no-state {{ROUTE_NAME}} target=<path> review-and-fix --assurance advisory --runtime-platform gemini --runtime-subagent-probe not-required --runtime-stdin-handoff not-required --runtime-downgrade-reason none --terminal-status unsupported --blocking-reason none --status-reason unsupported-runtime-capability --json

If the user requests strict verified assurance, explain that Gemini remains advisory-only and do not issue a strict verified workflow command.

Read-only advisory flow:
1. Confirm real stdin handoff before semantic payload commands: start the command as a process/session, obtain a stdin handle, write payload bytes, send EOF, and read exit code plus stdout/stderr.
2. On stdin handoff failure, fail closed as unsafe-handoff-file before semantic handoff. Do not use shell pipes, heredocs, herestrings, command substitution, argv, environment variables, env vars, or raw temp files for semantic payloads.
3. Start review-backed no-state context:

drfx workflow context --no-state {{ROUTE_NAME}} target=<path> read-only --assurance advisory --runtime-platform gemini --runtime-subagent-probe not-required --runtime-stdin-handoff ready --runtime-downgrade-reason none --phase initial-review --json

4. Keep reviewGuard and stateToken in coordinator memory only. Never write tokens to the filesystem and never hand-edit tokens.
5. Build the reviewer prompt in memory from the context skeleton plus target/reference reads. Gemini produces advisory review content; it must not claim workflow PASS.
6. Submit review, triage, and final response by repeating the same runtime fields:

drfx workflow record-review --no-state {{ROUTE_NAME}} target=<path> read-only --assurance advisory --runtime-platform gemini --runtime-subagent-probe not-required --runtime-stdin-handoff ready --runtime-downgrade-reason none --phase initial-review --review-guard <reviewGuard> --result-stdin --json
drfx workflow record-triage --no-state {{ROUTE_NAME}} target=<path> read-only --assurance advisory --runtime-platform gemini --runtime-subagent-probe not-required --runtime-stdin-handoff ready --runtime-downgrade-reason none --phase initial-review --state-token <latestStateToken> --triage-stdin --json
drfx workflow finalize --no-state {{ROUTE_NAME}} target=<path> read-only --assurance advisory --runtime-platform gemini --runtime-subagent-probe not-required --runtime-stdin-handoff ready --runtime-downgrade-reason none --state-token <latestStateToken> --final-response-stdin --json

No-state final status is read-only-clean, read-only-findings, blocked, or unsupported; never pass.

Embedded shared content:

{{EMBEDDED_SHARED_CONTENT}}
'''
